      "content": "that seems like a very optimistic way to look at it. but even with those policies, doesn't the sheer scale of these high-density developments often end up destroying the character of existing communities and pushing out long-term residents regardless of what the zoning says? it feels like the \"benefits\" you're describing are mostly for new developers and high-income professionals coming in.",
